The paper discusses the concept of explainable artificial intelligence (XAI) and how to evaluate the effectiveness of explanations for automated algorithmic data processing. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including human-computer interaction (cs.HC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), and cybersecurity (cs.CY). However, since the paper focuses on the user's ability to understand the explanations, cs.HC is the most likely sub-category.
